      <description>Biography I am a Research Assistant at the Networks group of Queen Mary University of London&amp;rsquo;s School of Electronic Engineering and Computer Science. My research interest includes Software Defined Networking, network simulation and inter-domain routing. I have a developer background, working in Open Source projects such as the implementation of OpenFlow 1.3, Route Flow and in the development of the winner OpenFlow driver on a competition organized by the Open Networking Foundation.</description>
